		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=12863"><span id=Sage>Kollins</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>198 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.01]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I'll just throw my 2cp in here although my rogue is only level 17...<br><br>STA affects HP AND if you have a stamina BELOW 100 you lose other melee stats when your stamina bar, the yellow one, drops down too low.&nbsp;&nbsp;The stamina loss isn't a giant factor for rogues because most rogues favor low weight weapons but it is something to consider because there are times, with a good group, where you will take on 7 or 8 mobs in a row and your stamina becomes important.  Stamina also affects hitpoints but if you are really after hitpoints you would probably have an easier time finding straight +hp gear than affecting your hp significantly with your stamina stat.<br><br>AGI affects your AC, this is also the major stat that goes down like the titanic when your stamina or health drop too low.  There isn't really a big difference in AC until your agi dips below 75, then you may as well be a wizard in cloth armor because everything that swings at you seems to hit.<br><br>STR affects damage output and carrying capacity, the later is obvious but the former can be a little deceiving.  Before you reach the damage cap (level 20?) strength affects only your average damage per hit, but once you break out of the damage cap you will find that anything that raises strength will also raise your average AND your max damage, including backstabs.<br><br>DEX affects weapon procs.  It also seems that dex affects the success and increases in defensive skills like dodge and parry.<br><br>Most of your melee stats will not make a huge difference unless they dip below 75 or go above 100.  For any tank class I'm under the impression that your goal should be 100str 100sta 100agi and 100dex then your next goal should be to raise str and dex as high as possible.  This is just the impression that I've gotten from playing them and others will most likely tell you different.  For rogues I'd say that stamina will be less important because of the light weapons that we tend to use, but there are still times where you will run out of stamina and start getting hit hard by mobs as your agility drops, those times are usually the ones where your group gets swarmed and the tanks are more worried about keeping mobs off the healers than off you.<br><br>My 2cp on classes is this: I picked half elf because of the well rounded stats and they are a pretty well liked race across Norrath but I'd also recomend a barbarian because of the strength and racial slam (anyone think they could racial slam a mob then strafe around them in time for a backstab?!), although there are obvious reasons to be a halfling, or a woodelf, or whatever class you want.  I really wouldn't recomend dark elf unless you want to be evil because of the way you are treated in most good cities and because of the mask of the deceiver but it is a viable option.   BTW sneak is a level 1 rogue skill and hide is a level 3 skill so unless you really want to be able to evade off your fellow newbies for your first 2 levels I'd say that isn't an outstanding reason to pick a class with racial hide, although your hide skill will be about 50 or so until you pass level 9 if you do pick one of those races.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
